    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a collector-grade 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2) in impeccable condition. This widebody variant features the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine, which has been meticulously maintained with a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recent Rear Main Seal (RMS) replacement. The G96 six-speed manual transaxle provides precise gate engagement, paired with a viscous-coupling AWD system for superior lateral grip. The suspension has been optimized with Bilstein PSS10 adjustable coilovers, while the braking system utilizes factory-spec Brembo four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors for maximum heat dissipation. The paint retains full depth and luster with zero evidence of track-use rock chips, and the DME report shows no over-revs in ranges 1 or 2. This is a turn-key, mechanically flawless example for the discerning purist.",
